audio Music "res://DialogicStuff/CopyrightFreeAudio/room_loop.mp3" [volume="-20.0" bus="" loop="true"]
if {Pronouns} == "They/Them":
	The nights were never easy for them. The memories of the city, its nauseating smells and images are hard to forget, even now as they’re surrounded by silence.
elif {Pronouns} == "He/Him":
	The nights were never easy for him. The memories of the city, its nauseating smells and images are hard to forget, even now as he’s surrounded by silence.
elif {Pronouns} == "She/Her":
	The nights were never easy for her. The memories of the city, its nauseating smells and images are hard to forget, even now as she’s surrounded by silence.
audio LongSFX "res://DialogicStuff/CopyrightFreeAudio/Ambiance_Forest_Birds_Loop_Stereo.wav" [loop="false"]
A single bird starts chirping outside the window.
Bezi: [i]*sigh* …My body feels stiff. As always. And my brain hurts from dreaming.[/i]
Bezi: [i]I have to get up. Marianna didn’t give me the diner for it to rot away, right? Speaking of Marianna, I wonder if she’s ready to go. I should bid her farewell.[/i]
if {Pronouns} == "They/Them":
	{PlayerName} gets all their strength to stand up and put on clean clothes. The new person in the village has to make the right impression.
	They head to the diner.
elif {Pronouns} == "She/Her":
	{PlayerName} gets all her strength to stand up and put on clean clothes. The new gal in the village has to make the right impression.
	She heads to the diner.
elif {Pronouns} == "He/Him":
	{PlayerName} gets all his strength to stand up and put on clean clothes. The new guy in the village has to make the right impression.
	He heads to the diner.
audio LongSFX -
audio "res://DialogicStuff/CopyrightFreeAudio/walk-down-the-stairs.mp3"
[background arg="res://assets/art/environments/diner_day.jpg" fade="0.0"]
audio Music "res://DialogicStuff/CopyrightFreeAudio/jazz-background-music.mp3" [volume="-20.0" bus="" loop="true"]
Bezi: [i]I was right about the creaking floor yesterday evening, but now that it’s brighter I can see how worn out they really are.[/i]
Bezi: [i]I should ask the lumberjack and get them replaced. The pantry might need a bit of supplying too. After all, I have to feed the entire village. I could ask around the square for some fresh produce.[/i]
Bezi: [i]It’s still early enough. I don’t expect any clients so early in the morning.[/i]
- GO TO THE LUMBER
	[background arg="res://assets/art/environments/forrest _maybe.png" fade="0.0"]
	audio Music "res://DialogicStuff/CopyrightFreeAudio/Gentle Breeze.mp3" [volume="0.0" bus="" loop="true"]
	audio LongSFX "res://DialogicStuff/CopyrightFreeAudio/Ambiance_Wind_Forest_Loop_Stereo.wav" [volume="-10.0" bus="" loop="true"]
	if {Pronouns} == "They/Them":
		Hubanka borders a huge forest from the south. {PlayerName} would often play there with other children when they were young, despite the adults telling them it’s easy to get lost there. A fellow lumberjack would nag the children for losing their way, but was always kind enough to walk them to the market square safely.
	elif {Pronouns} == "She/Her":
		Hubanka borders a huge forest from the south. {PlayerName} would often play there with other children when she was young, despite the adults telling them it’s easy to get lost there. A fellow lumberjack would nag the children for losing their way, but was always kind enough to walk them to the market square safely.
	elif {Pronouns} == "He/Him":
		Hubanka borders a huge forest from the south. {PlayerName} would often play there with other children when he was young, despite the adults telling them it’s easy to get lost there. A fellow lumberjack would nag the children for losing their way, but was always kind enough to walk them to the market square safely.
	The lumberjack was old, but it’s possible one of his sons took over the business.
	{PlayerName} looks around and notices a trail in the moss by the path.
	Bezi: [i]Looks like someone’s already been picking mushrooms today. Had to be someone experienced - Mushrooms are easy to miss under the moss, and if you’re not aware they’re there, then how are you going to pick them?[/i]
	Bezi: My parents taught me some tricks to distinguish which mushrooms are edible. Maybe I’ll spot some on the way to the lumber… If there are any left, that is…
	Bezi: Hm?
	What’s that sound?
	audio LongSFX "res://DialogicStuff/CopyrightFreeAudio/whistling-tune.mp3"
	A quiet tune wanders in the morning wind. {PlayerName} goes slowly in the direction of the sound and sees a man sitting under the tree, fiddling with something in his fingers.
	He looks old, but he doesn’t resemble any of the senior folks we used to know. Perhaps that’s the mushroom connoisseur.
	The man’s face is not clearly visible because of his ginormous red moustache and beard. His clothes are shabby, but what piques {PlayerName}’s interest is a necklace with a symbol - a peace sign. Some youngsters in the city wore a similar one.
	He seemed to notice us staring and waves at us slowly.
	audio LongSFX -
	join Hippie center [extra_data="set Mood/Base"]
	Hippie: Welcome, stranger! What brings you to this haven?
	Hippie: Are you a traveller? Came to see the village? I don’t think I’ve seen you around before…
	His calm and intriguingly monotone voice immediately sparks a memory - This is Richard, the boy who spent all days reading books he got from Mrs. Barbara. He never really got along with other kids his age.
	No wonder he prefers the sylvan solitude than the village square. Why does he look so much older though?
	if {Pronouns} == "They/Them":
		Richard takes a second to huff some smoke from his blunt. The smell makes {PlayerName} dizzy. No wonder they didn’t recognize him - That smoke could change a newborn into a grown adult in seconds.
	elif {Pronouns} == "She/Her":
		Richard takes a second to huff some smoke from his blunt. The smell makes {PlayerName} dizzy. No wonder she didn’t recognize him - That smoke could change a newborn into a grown adult in seconds.
	elif {Pronouns} == "He/Him":
		Richard takes a second to huff some smoke from his blunt. The smell makes {PlayerName} dizzy. No wonder he didn’t recognize him - That smoke could change a newborn into a grown adult in seconds.
	Bezi: Um, hi! You might not remember me, but I’m {PlayerName}, Marianna’s cousin… You- you know Marianna, right? Wojciech’s daughter?
	Richard is staring at you blankly for a mere second.
	Hippie: No.
	A straightforward answer.
	Bezi: The guy who owned a diner.
	update Hippie [animation="Tada" length="0.1" extra_data="set Mood/Happy"]
	Hippie: Ooooh, you should’ve said that sooner! I loved that diner! They served the best mushroom alfredo in the area! I love mushrooms, so I often come here to pick them. Look.
	Richard reaches for a wicker basket from behind his back and shows {PlayerName} his collection.
	He really knows his mushrooms. Specimens like these would easily land on a plate in a 5-star city restaurant.
	update Hippie [animation="Tada" length="0.1" extra_data="set Mood/Pensive"]
	Hippie: Too bad the diner’s been closed for a while now… They could make something tasty with these.
	Bezi: Actually, I’m the new owner. I was going to the lumber for new planks, but saw you instead-
	update Hippie [animation="Tada" length="0.1" extra_data="set Mood/Base"]
	Hippie: Take these then.
	Richard shoves a basket into {PlayerName}’s hands without hesitation. He’s a VERY straightforward guy. But he’s also right - {PlayerName} could make something delicious from them. It’s a tempting offer.
	- ACCEPT (+30 mushrooms)
		Bezi: Well… Thank you, Richard. I should be back at the diner in a few hours. If you have time, do come by. I’ll think of something we could do with these.
		update Hippie [animation="Tada" length="0.1" extra_data="set Mood/Happy"]
		Richard smiles warmly. It’s clear he’s excited to try the new dish.
	- DENY (+15 mushrooms)
		Bezi: W-what?! No, I can’t take them, I’m sorry. You probably took your sweet time to pick all of this. You should have some for yourself, Richard.
		Hippie: Take at least half of them. What am I supposed to do with all this?
		if {Pronouns} == "They/Them":
			Eating so many mushrooms would definitely kill his liver faster than the blunts would. As there’s no point arguing with him, {PlayerName} takes half of the mushrooms and shoves them into their pockets.
		elif {Pronouns} == "She/Her":
			Eating so many mushrooms would definitely kill his liver faster than the blunts would. As there’s no point arguing with him, {PlayerName} takes half of the mushrooms and shoves them into her pockets.
		elif {Pronouns} == "He/Him":
			Eating so many mushrooms would definitely kill his liver faster than the blunts would. As there’s no point arguing with him, {PlayerName} takes half of the mushrooms and shoves them into his pockets.
	update Hippie [animation="Tada" length="0.1" extra_data="set Mood/Base"]
	Hippie: By the way, you should call me Richie. That’s what everyone calls me.
	If you ever need advice on mushroom-hunting in the future, find me. I can show you so many of them - sweet, bitter, brown or blue!
	Hippie: I also saw a very strange one down the path by the lake. But I’m not sure if it’s edible. I’ve only seen such a mushroom in one book.
	Hippie: Though, it was a science-fiction novel from the 20s… It was a brain-eating mushroom who controlled people to make it reproduce and take over the whole universe. *chuckle*
	Hippie: But there’s no mushroom like that. I would know about it.
	A brain-eating mushroom. That’s an interesting concept for a story.
	There is an awkward silence between the two. While Richie surely doesn’t believe in such monstrosities, {PlayerName}’s mind is intrigued. To say the least.
	update Hippie [animation="Tada" length="0.1" extra_data="set Mood/Happy"]
	if {Pronouns} == "They/Them":
		With a smile, Richie waves them goodbye as {PlayerName} leaves for the lumber.
	elif {Pronouns} == "She/Her":
		With a smile, Richie waves her goodbye as {PlayerName} leaves for the lumber.
	elif {Pronouns} == "He/Him":
		With a smile, Richie waves him goodbye as {PlayerName} leaves for the lumber.
	leave Hippie
- GO TO THE SQUARE MARKET
	[background arg="res://assets/art/environments/village_square_day.jpg" fade="0.0"]
	audio Music "res://DialogicStuff/CopyrightFreeAudio/folk_acoustic-village.mp3" [volume="-15.0" bus="" loop="true"]
	audio LongSFX "res://DialogicStuff/CopyrightFreeAudio/freesound_crowd_talking_poland-old-market.mp3" [volume="0.0" bus="" loop="true"]
	The square, as in every village, is the heart of the community.
	People come here for various reasons - to talk, to play, to sit on the bench and admire the blue sky, or, like {PlayerName} to buy supplies.
	The vendors come and go all the time, but one gentleman stays in Hubanka no matter the weather - Mr. Kabanos, with his freshly-picked vegetables and fruit.
	join Kabanos center
	Bezi: Hello, Sir. I’m {PlayerName}, new owner of the diner. Since it’s gonna be open again, I wanted to buy some necessities.
	Kabanos: Aye, welcome! Pick whichever you need. Picked everything straight from the farmers. You won’t find fresher produce in the area, I’ll tell ya that.
	label MARKET TUTORIAL (-x coins)
	Bezi: Thanks a lot! You should come by the diner sometime, once you’re off work that is. I’ll try to do these products justice- \
	*Ugh*
	if {Pronouns} == "They/Them":
		{PlayerName} suddenly feels a putrid stench behind their back. Alcohol mixed with… God knows what other substance.
	elif {Pronouns} == "She/Her":
		{PlayerName} suddenly feels a putrid stench behind her back. Alcohol mixed with… God knows what other substance.
	elif {Pronouns} == "He/Him":
		{PlayerName} suddenly feels a putrid stench behind his back. Alcohol mixed with… God knows what other substance.
	join Zdzichu right [extra_data="set Mood/Drunk"]
	Zdzichu: ‘Ello, Boss! You got a coin by any chance?
	Kabanos: Go away, old drunkie.
	Zdzichu: I ain’t talking to you, meathead.
	leave Kabanos [animation="Fade Out"]
	update Zdzichu center [move_time="1.0"]
	if {Pronouns} == "They/Them":
		The old man appears to be talking to {PlayerName}, as they’re the only one at the stall except Mr. Kabanos.
	elif {Pronouns} == "She/Her":
		The old man appears to be talking to {PlayerName}, as she’s the only one at the stall except Mr. Kabanos.
	elif {Pronouns} == "He/Him":
		The old man appears to be talking to {PlayerName}, as he’s the only one at the stall except Mr. Kabanos.
	The man’s most likely homeless, by the look of his clothes and, well… smell.
	Times are hard, and {PlayerName} knows this too well. The city’s misery seems to be moving to the nearby villages.
	if {Pronouns} == "They/Them":
		They could help him. One coin is not a fortune, but one can never be sure what it will be really spent on.
	elif {Pronouns} == "She/Her":
		She could help him. One coin is not a fortune, but one can never be sure what it will be really spent on.
	elif {Pronouns} == "He/Him":
		He could help him. One coin is not a fortune, but one can never be sure what it will be really spent on.
	- YES (-1 coin)
		Bezi: Here you go, sir.
		update Zdzichu [animation="Tada" length="0.1" extra_data="set Mood/Happy"]
		Zdzichu: Ohohoho, cheers, Boss.
		Zdzichu: Do say - Would you like an old man to tell ya a story?
		- SURE, WHY NOT?
			update Zdzichu [animation="Tada" length="0.1" extra_data="set Mood/Base"]
			Zdzichu: Well, sit your bottocks down, ‘cause this is gonna get interesting.
			Zdzichu: *clears throat* LONG AGO… In this very place, which we now call Hubanka, used to live an old witch.
			Zdzichu: In the forest, I mean, not [i]here[/i], ‘cause people didn’t like her much. Anyway.
			Zdzichu: She had a lush garden growing behind her cottage. Just as lush as her [i]other[/i] garden. Don’t ask how I know, I just do.
			Zdzichu: And in that garden there grew different plants - From nettle to peonies to mushrooms of all kinds.
			Zdzichu: But, one day, one of the mushrooms grew out of control. It grew so big that it [i]ATE[/i] her cottage with the witch inside.
			Zdzichu: I guess the witch wasn’t dead enough, ‘cause some time after the dinner, the mushroom started talking with her.
			Zdzichu: It grew a brain smart enough to think on its own. The two became friends, which is stupid if you ask me. I’d be pretty mad at it. I wouldn’t say a word to that greedy shit.
			Zdzichu: And here they were - A witch feared by everyone, and a shitty overgrown mushroom who could talk. As if the world wasn’t fucked up enough.
			Zdzichu: They had a plan. To take revenge on everyone who ever doubted the witch. And…
			Zdzichu: They infected everyone with the mushroom’s spores! Lads started acting like zombies. The mushroom was IN CONTROL OF THEM.
			update Zdzichu [animation="Tada" length="0.1" extra_data="set Mood/Happy"]
			Zdzichu: IT MADE AN ARMY OF MINDLESS SHROOMS. GET IT? HAHAHAHA
			…Seems like that coin will be well spent on more alcohol, as if there wasn’t enough in his brain to think of that story.
			update Zdzichu [animation="Tada" length="0.1" extra_data="set Mood/Base"]
			Zdzichu: My advice for you, Boss - Keep. Away. From. Mushrooms.
			Zdzichu: You’ll thank me for it.
		- NO, THANKS. I’M RATHER BUSY.
			update Zdzichu [animation="Tada" length="0.1" extra_data="set Mood/Base"]
			Zdzichu: You don’t know what you’re missing, kid.
			Zdzichu: Lemme just tell ya - The mushrooms are coming.
			Zdzichu: Better watch out for yourself, hm?
		The old man walks away looking behind at {PlayerName} every few steps.
